      "amount": "1/4 cup, chopped"
    },
    {
      "name": "Salt",
      "amount": "to taste"
    },
    {
      "name": "Black Pepper",
      "amount": "to taste"
    },
    {
      "name": "Feta Cheese (optional)",
      "amount": "1/2 cup, crumbled"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the sliced red onion and cook until slightly caramelized, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the sliced zucchini and red bell pepper, and cook for an additional 4-5 minutes.",
    "In a separate saucepan, combine the cannellini beans, vinegar, garlic, salt, and black pepper. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until heated through.",
    "To assemble the dish, divide the bean mixture among four plates, followed by a portion of the grilled vegetables.",
    "Drizzle the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil over the vegetables and sprinkle with chopped parsley.",
    "If using feta cheese, crumble it on top of the vegetables.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
  ],
